<headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 27 at 8:43PM EDT  by NWS Baltimore/Washington</headline>
<description>...ENHANCED THREAT FOR THE SPREAD OF WILDFIRES MONDAY...
Minimum relative humidity will drop to between 15 and 20 percent
across central Virginia while northwest winds gust frequently
between 20 and 30 mph. The strongest winds will coincide with the
lowest humidity during the afternoon and early evening hours.
Fuel moisture will continue to dry out during this time, and the
combination of low fuel moisture, low relative humidity, and gusty
winds will enhance the threat for the spread of wildfires.
Outdoor burning is strongly discouraged during this time. Please
refer to your local burn permitting authority on whether you can
burn. If you do burn, use extreme caution and ensure fire
suppression is readily available.</description>
